    {
      "id": "Ugx82JbX4bSCE9yakXl4AaABAg",
      "author": "@randydaniels6501",
      "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_lMoH-kt98SsWY6qulhKaQfqRWR8zAA8tp6zj0tO2g=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
      "text": "In 1970, I joined the Marines, after high school graduation in May, specifically to fight in Vietnam. After boot camp of a speedy 9 weeks, we went to Okinawa, Japan, into scuba recon and I loved it, being in and having to do with the water/ocean, being coming a swimmer of the 6 man rubber recon raft and all this took place at Camp Swab, one of 2 military camps, the other being Camp Hansen. Where I was at, the ocean was approximately 10 to 12 ffoot deep and clearer than glass! The fish were exotic colors, solid blue, solid red, solid yellow, all types were amazingly beautiful! ust before preparing for Cebu, Philippines, our orders were changed to Vietnam, but it didn't mattr, I was gung ho! But I'll never fforget my time in Okinanawa, loved it! For the past 28 years now, I've lived on the island of Aruba, having the same feeling about the ocean!",
      "likeCount": 7,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-18T19:11:08Z",
      "replyCount": 2,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "Ugx82JbX4bSCE9yakXl4AaABAg.AZQ0ZyawuNvAZUCOBRIT5m",
